<title>helios::engine::game::systems</title><para>Global game systems that operate on the GameWorld rather than individual GameObjects.</para>
<para>Systems are ideal for cross-cutting concerns that span multiple entities, such as object pooling, physics simulation, or collision detection. They receive frame updates via the <computeroutput>Updatable</computeroutput> interface and have access to the full <computeroutput>GameWorld</computeroutput> context.</para>
